  "prompt": "Is it normal to have no dreams while sleeping?",
  "response": "Yes, it is normal for some people to feel as though they have no dreams while sleeping. In reality, most people do dream during the rapid eye movement (REM) stage of sleep, but not everyone remembers their dreams upon waking. The ability to recall dreams can vary based on several factors, such as the depth of sleep, stress levels, sleep disorders, and individual differences in brain activity. If you have concerns about your sleep patterns or dream recall, consider discussing them with a healthcare professional.",
